The paper deals with the complexity of Turing machines, which is a central topic in computational complexity theory (cs.CC). The study of space-time diagrams and fractal dimensions is related to the analysis of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS). The use of empirical verification and partial proofs suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the connection between fractal dimension and process complexity may have implications for systems and control theory (cs.SY).
